{"cursor":"12967","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn mathematics, specifically in category theory, an 'additive category' is a\npreadditive category 'C' such that all finite collections of objects\nof 'C' have a biproduct in 'C'.\n\nA category 'C' is preadditive if all its hom-sets are Abelian groups and\ncomposition of morphisms is bilinear; in other words, 'C' is enriched over the\nmonoidal category of Abelian groups. A biproduct in a preadditive category is\nboth a finitary product and a finitary coproduct.\n","linknr":156,"url":"Additive_category","recorded":1362902621,"links":11,"instances":["mathematics","algebra","mathematics","category_theory","mathematics","category_theory","category_theory","mathematics","mathematics","mathematics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Additive categories|"],"headings":["Definition","Examples","Internal characterisation of the addition law","Matrix representation of morphisms","Additive functors","Special cases","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/3/e/d3eb1f85f9f29f0e66289b4d039390da.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/4/d/64dcc9361228d206f106c5399c4eb94b.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/9/2/a92156752c51695da70cf3ef6be41639.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["product","category_theory"],["ring","mathematics"],["field","mathematics"],["matrix","mathematics"],["matrix","mathematics"],["matrix","mathematics"],["dimension","mathematics"],["ring","mathematics"],["0","number"],["set","mathematics"],["module","mathematics"],["zero_object","algebra"],["kernel","category_theory"],["cokernel","category_theory"]],"members":["ring","zero_object","matrix","kernel","dimension","product","cokernel","field","set","module"],"related":["Mathematics","Category_theory","Preadditive_category","Biproduct","Hom-set","A